'''[[Olbers]]' [[paradox]]'''
#{{astronomy}} the [[observation]] that the [[night]] [[sky]] is mostly [[dark]], yet, in a [[boundless]] [[universe]] of [[star]]s, every [[line of sight]] from the [[eye]] must eventually [[intercept]] the [[surface]] of a star

